President Obama hosted over 250 bipartisan Mayors at the White House during their annual U.S. Conference of Mayors (USCM) Winter Meeting. The President thanked the Mayors for their partnerships and outlined the Administration's priorities for cities in the year ahead. The meeting focused on the economic progress made by each city since Obama took office. The Mayors discussed various topics including criminal justice reform, advanced manufacturing, the Trans-Pacific Partnership, education, veterans homelessness, minimum wage, climate and energy, transportation and infrastructure, smart cities, the Affordable Care Act, My Brother's Keeper, and immigration. Mayors shared the ways they are implementing Obama's agenda in their cities.